<br>
Are you telling me after said patch corrupts the Direct X drivers for everyone using ATI video cards prior to the 8500 series is bad customer support.  <br>
<br>
Are you telling me after two weeks, after another major patch, they send a blanket e-mail message saying it was a temporary problem and try it again which of course does not fix it is bad customer support. <br>
<br>
Are you telling me that waiting three weeks for a response to a post asking for help on their Technical Help board, they refuse to give you any answer even though they have responded to posts posted just before yours and just after yours is bad customer support. <br>
<br>
I have never gotten any help from SOE customer support and I don't expect to ever get any.  I don't know how you can get worse than that. <br>
<br>
Oh wait, once I was getting kicked to the desktop while zoning while on the boats in Ocean of Tears.  Of course, by the time I could get back on, I was back in Ocean of Tears.  After this happened the third time, I went to the On-line chat for help and reported the problem.  The Tech couldn't help me and ended the conversation by saying  &quot;I guess you will just have to ride the boats.  hehehehe&quot; <br>
<br>
That is worse.  <br>
<br>
Of course the GM never answered my petition.  I finally got out of OOT by repeatly camping until I zoned in from the camp in Butcherblock Mountains.  {I had bound myself in OOT because I was hunting the AC and could not gate out.}<br>
